IS-A RelationShip: can access by creating an object in extended class(i.e child class). 
it is used for code re-usability in java.

for example:
a potato is vegetable, a Bus is a vehicle, a bulb is a electronic device etc.

Has-A relationship is also known as composition. it is used for code re-usability in java.

for example:
a car has a engine, a dog has a tail and so on.



Access modifiers:

Access Modifiers helps to restrict the scope of a class, constructor, variable, method 
or a data member.

there are four access modifier available in java:

1: Default (accessible only within the same package)
2: Private (accessible only within same class)
3: Protected (accessible only within same package or subclass in different package)
4: Public (accessible from everywhere)